From 85e100d87198b998b9ed1ea76c1a28b5894a4dbc Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Daniel Golle <daniel@makrotopia.org>
Date: Tue, 24 Feb 2026 15:48:12 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 07/24] build: make device-mapper support optional
 (HAVE_DEVMAPPER)

Introduce a HAVE_DEVMAPPER feature flag to both meson and autoconf
build systems, allowing cryptsetup to be built without libdevmapper.

Meson: add a 'devmapper' feature option (auto by default). When the
dependency is not found or explicitly disabled, set
conf.set10('HAVE_DEVMAPPER', false) and skip HAVE_DECL_* checks.
All tools (cryptsetup, veritysetup, integritysetup) are still built;
operations requiring device-mapper will fail at runtime with -ENOTSUP.

Autoconf: add --disable-devmapper flag with auto/yes/no semantics.
When disabled or not found, skip PKG_CHECK_MODULES, AC_CHECK_DECLS,
and static library detection for devmapper.

Guard the full libdevmapper.c implementation behind #if HAVE_DEVMAPPER
and provide stub functions (returning -ENOTSUP/NULL/0) in the #else
branch, following the existing pattern from utils_blkid.c.
